The paper focuses on Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new module for learning cross-modality relationships, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modality features, which could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
